SIMPLE: subtle
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subtle
<hw>Sub"tle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Subtler</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Subtlest</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</amorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>sotil</ets>, <ets>subtil</ets>, OF. <ets>soutil</ets>, later
<ets>subtil</ets>, F. <ets>subtil</ets>, L. <ets>subtilis</ets>;
probably, originally, woven fine, and fr. <ets>sub</ets> under +
<ets>tela</ets> a web, fr. <ets>texere</ets> to weave. See
<er>Text</er>, and cf. <er>Subtile</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Sly in
design; artful; cunning; insinuating; subtile; -- applied to persons;
<as>as, a <ex>subtle</ex> foe</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>subtle</xex>
traitor.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Cunningly devised; crafty; treacherous; <as>as, a
<ex>subtle</ex> stratagem</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Characterized by refinement and niceness in drawing
distinctions; nicely discriminating; -- said of persons; <as>as, a
<ex>subtle</ex> logician</as>; refined; tenuous; sinuous; insinuating;
hence, penetrative or pervasive; -- said of the mind; its faculties, or
its operations; <as>as, a <ex>subtle</ex> intellect; a <ex>subtle</ex>
imagination; a <ex>subtle</ex> process of thought</as>; also, difficult
of apprehension; elusive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Things remote from use, obscure and <qex>subtle</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Smooth and deceptive.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Like to a bowl upon a <qex>subtle</qex> ground [bowling
ground].</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Artful; crafty; cunning; shrewd; sly; wily.</syn>
<usage> <xex>Subtle</xex> is the most comprehensive of these epithets
and implies the finest intellectual quality. See <er>Shrewd</er>, and
<er>Cunning</er>.</usage>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1438 --></p>

<p><ent>Subtleness</ent>⟦br⟧
